The paper deals with the field of Text-to-Speech (TTS) which is related to speech synthesis and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound) which deals with audio and speech processing. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which is a common theme in the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of latent variables, which is a common theme in the sub-category cs.LG (Learning). The paper also mentions the development of controllable speech synthesis systems, which is a common theme in the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the use of expressive speech, which is a common theme in the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
